Uses of Package
lombok.core

  • Packages that use lombok.core 
    Package Description
    lombok
    This package contains all the annotations and support classes you need as a user of lombok.
    lombok.bytecode
    This package contains utilities and handlers for the 'post-process class files' aspect of lombok.
    lombok.core
    Contains the platform-agnostic core of lombok.
    lombok.core.configuration  
    lombok.core.handlers
    This package contains utility methods and classes shared between javac-specific feature implementations and eclipse-specific feature implementations.
    lombok.core.runtimeDependencies
    This package is the basis for lombok's (the jar, run as an application) ability to spin off a clone of itself that only contains files required as a runtime dependency.
    lombok.delombok  
    lombok.eclipse
    Includes the eclipse-specific implementations of the lombok AST and annotation introspection support.
    lombok.eclipse.agent
    Contains the mechanism that instruments eclipse by being loaded as a javaagent.
    lombok.eclipse.handlers
    Contains the classes that implement the transformations for all of lombok's various features on the eclipse platform.
    lombok.eclipse.handlers.singulars  
    lombok.installer
    This package contains the lombok installer.
    lombok.javac
    Includes the javac specific implementations of the lombok AST and annotation introspection support.
    lombok.javac.apt
    Contains the mechanism that instruments javac as an annotation processor.
    lombok.javac.handlers
    Contains the classes that implement the transformations for all of lombok's various features on the javac v1.6 platform.
    lombok.javac.handlers.singulars

  • Classes in lombok.core used by lombok.core 
    Class and Description
    AnnotationValues
    Represents a single annotation in a source file and can be used to query the parameters present on it.
    AnnotationValues.AnnotationValue
    Represents a single method on the annotation class.
    AST
    Lombok wraps the AST produced by a target platform into its own AST system, mostly because both Eclipse and javac do not allow upward traversal (from a method to its owning type, for example).
    AST.Kind
    The kind of node represented by a given AST.Node object.
    DiagnosticsReceiver 
    FieldAugment 
    ImportList 
    LombokApp
    Implement this class, and add yourself as a provider for it, to become an app runnable by running lombok.jar as a jar.
    LombokImmutableList 
    LombokNode
    An instance of this class wraps an Eclipse/javac internal node object.
    TypeLibrary
    Library of types, which can be used to look up potential matching types.
